# Verify Sonarqube Changes

This skill verifies all the sonarqube changes done and posts an update.

## Parameters

- `repo`: The repo where changes were made
- `jira_ticket`: The jira ticket listing all the sonarqube issues where update needs to be posted

## Steps

1. Check SonarQube for the PR analysis. If there are any new issues introduced by the fixes, fix those too and repeat the build verification until SonarQube shows 0 new issues on the PR. 

2. Commit all changes as new commits, not REBASE, push the branch

3. Post a comment on the Jira ticket summarizing: SonarQube before/after metrics, number of issues fixed, effort saved, rules addressed, what remains and why, and verification results.
